<br>
This was longer than I played before packing it all up to be returned to EB.<br>
<br>
I really didn't like it. If you liked Baldur's Gate, I guess it'll be ok. I really hated the canned replies in single player. And it felt more like Gauntlet or Diablo than D&amp;D in gameplay. <br>
<br>
Among other things, it moves really really fast, fast enough that I don't think &quot;live GM'ing&quot; will be very viable. It's more of a hack and slash. Since this was the main reason I got it, I didn't see too much point in continuing.<br>
<br>
Lot of hype, but I was really underwhelmed. And no way I was going to keep it given the $55 (+books) cost. <p><table border=0 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=0><tr><td><img src="http://home.tampabay.rr.com/legolaas/images/numtini-100.jpg" width="52" height="100"></td><td><table style="font-family:verdana,arial;" border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;"><A HREF="http://pub94.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN" title="<insert popup caption here>" style="color:#ff0000;font-weight:700;">Numtini Lightheart</A></td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;">47th Season Gnome of Death</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;">Member, <A HREF="http://pub96.ezboard.com/beqcivismacto" title="Civis Macto Website" style="color:#ff0000;">Civis Macto</A></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
